This is a DEVELOPMENT/BETA project and will undergo numerous revisions.
NCBI is experimenting with different approaches to organize prokaryotic genomes in sequence-related groups. 
The current approach is based on the comparison of universally conserved markers. 
See marker data at ftp://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/genomes/GENOME_REPORTS/MARKERS/


====================================
Directory Content:
====================================
This FTP directory contains data for prokaryotic genomes organized in species-level groups (clades)
File Name              File Content
--------------------------------------------------------------

Phyla.txt:   		phyla and superphyla as defined by NCBI Taxonomy that contains at least one full genome assembly

Clade_*.txt: 		Clades are calculated separately for each phylum. 
	     		* - taxid of a phylum or superphylum. Each line represents genome assembly assigned to a clade
               
no_asignment.txt	genome assemblies for which clade cannot be assigned for various reasons
  
====================================
File formats and column description:
====================================

The first line of each file provides column header names and not data.

The following file definitions are formatted as:
  Column Name | Description

------------------
Phyla.txt file:
------------------
Taxonomy ID		phylum or superphylum NCBI Taxonomy numeric identifier
Taxonomy name		phylum or superphylum scientific name
Taxonomy rank		NCBI TAxonomy rank - phylum or superphylum
Superkingdom name	Archaea or Bacteria
#Genomes		total number of genome assemblies in a phylum/superphylum assigned to a clade
#Clades			total number of clades in a phylum/superphylum

------------------
Clade_*.txt file:
------------------
Clade ID		unique numeric calde identifier
Taxonomy ID		Taxonomy ID of the assembly
BioProject ID		BioProject for GenBank assembly
BioSample ID		BioSample ID for GenBank assembly
Assembly ID		Assembly ID for GenBank assembly
Nucleotide accession(s)	GenBank accession(s), comma separated. For WGS assemblies only wgs-master accession is shown

